Template Literals: strings allowing embedded expressions
-Multi-line strings and string interpolation with template literals
-previous ES5 called it template strings
-Enclosed with back ticks `` instead of either quotes '' OR ""
  eg:
  `howdy cowboy`
  `hello
   to you!`
  `hello ${name}`

Strings: global object constructor for sequence of characters
-Useful for holding representable data in text form
-Common operations include, .length(check their length), build and concatenate with + AND += operators
-Character Access:
  1. charAt(i) returns value at index specified
  2. 'string'[i] returns value at index specified
-String has many useful methods including: .toUpperCase(), .toLowerCase(), .slice()
